title: 24 Hours In The Past
description:
History Documentary hosted by Ruth Goodman and Fi Glover, published by BBC in 2015 - English narration 

24 Hours In The Past a Documentary in which six celebrities travel back in time to the 19th century, spending four full days experiencing the relentless graft of the working poor in Victorian Britain. Impressionist Alistair McGowan, former minister Ann Widdecombe, actress Zoe Lucker, world champion hurdler Colin Jackson, actor Tyger Drew-Honey and presenter Miquita Oliver are the volunteers
